<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{y}=-{24}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{y}=-{29}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+-{1}{y}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{24}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{24}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{\left(\frac{{-{24}-{\left(-{1}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}\right)}+-{1}{y}=-{29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{7}}{{6}}\cdot{\left(-{24}\right)}-\frac{{7}}{{6}}{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}=-{29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{28}-{\left({1.1666666666667}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}=-{29}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.1666666666667}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}=-{29}--{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.1666666666667}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({1.1666666666667}+{\left(-{1}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.16666666666667}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{1}}{{0.16666666666667}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+-{1}{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{\left({6}\right)}=-{24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{24}-{\left({6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{30}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

